WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.196 align:middle line:90%


00:00:09.196 --> 00:00:12.100 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:12.100 --> 00:00:14.050 align:middle line:90%


00:00:14.050 --> 00:00:17.800 align:middle line:84%
>> Any place there is beauty,
any place where there is

00:00:17.800 --> 00:00:22.410 align:middle line:84%
a delicious flavor, any place
where there is a word well

00:00:22.410 --> 00:00:27.040 align:middle line:84%
placed, that is an
occasion for devotion.

00:00:27.040 --> 00:00:30.463 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:30.463 --> 00:00:41.710 align:middle line:90%


00:00:41.710 --> 00:00:45.200 align:middle line:10%
>> With its astounding diversity
of religions, languages,

00:00:45.200 --> 00:00:48.520 align:middle line:10%
and cultures, everywhere you
look in this most ancient

00:00:48.520 --> 00:00:52.165 align:middle line:10%
and complex of countries, India
seems steeped in devotion.

00:00:52.165 --> 00:00:54.900 align:middle line:90%


00:00:54.900 --> 00:00:58.170 align:middle line:10%
Yoga's oldest texts and
teachings trace their origins

00:00:58.170 --> 00:01:01.650 align:middle line:10%
here, perhaps the most
recognizable of which

00:01:01.650 --> 00:01:05.550 align:middle line:10%
is "The Bhagavad Gita," a
700-verse Hindu scripture that

00:01:05.550 --> 00:01:08.610 align:middle line:10%
takes up chapters 23
through 40 of the Hindu

00:01:08.610 --> 00:01:12.220 align:middle line:10%
epic, "Mahabharata."

00:01:12.220 --> 00:01:16.860 align:middle line:84%
>> Maha means great, and
bharata is a word for India.

00:01:16.860 --> 00:01:19.990 align:middle line:84%
And in this epic that's
seven times longer

00:01:19.990 --> 00:01:23.920 align:middle line:84%
than the "Iliad" and the
"Odyssey" combined, so many

00:01:23.920 --> 00:01:27.070 align:middle line:84%
of the narratives that
we experience today--

00:01:27.070 --> 00:01:29.590 align:middle line:84%
issues of gender,
issues of race, issues

00:01:29.590 --> 00:01:32.650 align:middle line:84%
of equality, issues
of human dignity--

00:01:32.650 --> 00:01:36.910 align:middle line:84%
all of these great themes are
found within the "Mahabharata."

00:01:36.910 --> 00:01:40.420 align:middle line:10%
>> Written during a time of
big change and social upheaval

00:01:40.420 --> 00:01:43.990 align:middle line:10%
in India, the "Bhagavad Gita"
portion of the "Mahabharata"

00:01:43.990 --> 00:01:47.020 align:middle line:10%
is about the search
for serenity, calmness,

00:01:47.020 --> 00:01:51.224 align:middle line:10%
and permanence in a
world of rapid change.

00:01:51.224 --> 00:01:54.970 align:middle line:84%
>> "Bhagavad Gita," this is
probably one of the main texts

00:01:54.970 --> 00:01:56.200 align:middle line:90%
of modern Hinduism.

00:01:56.200 --> 00:01:58.150 align:middle line:84%
It's an ancient text
and very important.

00:01:58.150 --> 00:02:01.990 align:middle line:84%
Every group, every
philosophical orientation,

00:02:01.990 --> 00:02:04.540 align:middle line:84%
every school of thought
has a "Bhagavad Gita"

00:02:04.540 --> 00:02:06.160 align:middle line:90%
as a central text.

00:02:06.160 --> 00:02:09.028 align:middle line:90%


00:02:09.028 --> 00:02:12.120 align:middle line:84%
That view that God
has become everything,

00:02:12.120 --> 00:02:14.380 align:middle line:84%
or everything we see is
only him or only her.

00:02:14.380 --> 00:02:15.180 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:02:15.180 --> 00:02:18.800 align:middle line:84%
[INAUDIBLE] That's held as
one of the highest experiences

00:02:18.800 --> 00:02:21.860 align:middle line:90%
in "The Bhagavad Gita."

00:02:21.860 --> 00:02:24.860 align:middle line:84%
>> Told through story
and song, The "Gita"

00:02:24.860 --> 00:02:28.580 align:middle line:84%
is a dialogue between Krishna,
considered God in the form

00:02:28.580 --> 00:02:34.250 align:middle line:84%
of man, and Arjuna, a hero
prince preparing for battle.

00:02:34.250 --> 00:02:38.810 align:middle line:84%
>> The great avatar, Krishna,
who says of himself that

00:02:38.810 --> 00:02:44.390 align:middle line:84%
whenever the world gets into
trouble, then I, as Vishnu,

00:02:44.390 --> 00:02:48.740 align:middle line:84%
embody myself forward as a
human being in order to restore

00:02:48.740 --> 00:02:51.960 align:middle line:90%
stability to a world gone awry.

00:02:51.960 --> 00:02:53.450 align:middle line:84%
And in this
particular narrative,

00:02:53.450 --> 00:03:00.950 align:middle line:84%
Arjuna has had a crisis and
has had so many life adventures

00:03:00.950 --> 00:03:04.730 align:middle line:84%
leading up to this horrific
war with his cousins,

00:03:04.730 --> 00:03:06.510 align:middle line:90%
and he loses his nerve.

00:03:06.510 --> 00:03:09.680 align:middle line:84%
He says, I don't
really want to do this

00:03:09.680 --> 00:03:14.270 align:middle line:84%
even though every circumstance
is mandating that he move

00:03:14.270 --> 00:03:17.600 align:middle line:90%
forward into this horrific war.

00:03:17.600 --> 00:03:20.570 align:middle line:84%
And what Krishna does is--
right at the beginning

00:03:20.570 --> 00:03:23.510 align:middle line:84%
the battle-- is sit
with him in the chariot

00:03:23.510 --> 00:03:29.420 align:middle line:84%
and give him chapter-by-chapter
counseling on how to move out

00:03:29.420 --> 00:03:31.700 align:middle line:84%
of a place of
self-identification

00:03:31.700 --> 00:03:36.260 align:middle line:84%
and self-pity into the state
of knowing that there's things

00:03:36.260 --> 00:03:40.790 align:middle line:84%
that we don't like to do that we
just simply move forward with,

00:03:40.790 --> 00:03:45.080 align:middle line:84%
not out of self-interest,
not out of hatred even,

00:03:45.080 --> 00:03:49.745 align:middle line:84%
but simply because
it's inevitable.

00:03:49.745 --> 00:03:53.000 align:middle line:84%
>> Krishna does advise Arjuna
that he should practice yoga

00:03:53.000 --> 00:03:58.940 align:middle line:84%
in order to make himself able to
fulfill his birth-given duties

00:03:58.940 --> 00:04:01.790 align:middle line:84%
with equanimity and without
regard for the results,

00:04:01.790 --> 00:04:04.690 align:middle line:84%
so that practicing breathing
techniques sitting down

00:04:04.690 --> 00:04:09.350 align:middle line:84%
in an asana meditating will
change his mind in such a way

00:04:09.350 --> 00:04:15.920 align:middle line:84%
that he can then go and fight
without concern for the result.

00:04:15.920 --> 00:04:19.490 align:middle line:10%
>> In just 18 brief
chapters, the "Bhagavad Gita"

00:04:19.490 --> 00:04:23.780 align:middle line:10%
is said to present three major
spiritual paths, or margas,

00:04:23.780 --> 00:04:26.030 align:middle line:10%
for each personality type.

00:04:26.030 --> 00:04:28.880 align:middle line:84%
>> It's actually a traditional
system of teaching and practice

00:04:28.880 --> 00:04:29.890 align:middle line:90%
called the margas.

00:04:29.890 --> 00:04:31.640 align:middle line:84%
And it's well described
in the scriptures.

00:04:31.640 --> 00:04:33.916 align:middle line:84%
And you could say each
path of yoga relates

00:04:33.916 --> 00:04:35.540 align:middle line:84%
to a different part
of our personality.

00:04:35.540 --> 00:04:38.462 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:38.462 --> 00:04:40.410 align:middle line:90%


00:04:40.410 --> 00:04:45.330 align:middle line:84%
>> Bhakti yoga is considered the
path of devotion; Karma yoga,

00:04:45.330 --> 00:04:49.530 align:middle line:84%
the path of selfless
action; and Jnana yoga,

00:04:49.530 --> 00:04:52.530 align:middle line:84%
the path of
self-transcending knowledge.

00:04:52.530 --> 00:04:55.650 align:middle line:84%
Some scholars would place
Raja among these paths,

00:04:55.650 --> 00:04:58.715 align:middle line:84%
but we explore Raja fully
in episode 5 of this series.

00:04:58.715 --> 00:05:01.425 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:05:01.425 --> 00:05:04.840 align:middle line:90%


00:05:04.840 --> 00:05:07.250 align:middle line:84%
>> Bhakti yoga, the
yoga of the heart,

00:05:07.250 --> 00:05:09.820 align:middle line:84%
meaning the heart is the
center of our emotions.

00:05:09.820 --> 00:05:12.520 align:middle line:84%
And Bhakti yoga is about how
to use that emotional energy

00:05:12.520 --> 00:05:15.640 align:middle line:84%
in a positive way,
which we call devotion.

00:05:15.640 --> 00:05:18.880 align:middle line:84%
So that's a very powerful force
that can really take us forward

00:05:18.880 --> 00:05:21.190 align:middle line:90%
in our spiritual evolution.

00:05:21.190 --> 00:05:23.770 align:middle line:84%
>> It's the yoga
of loving devotion,

00:05:23.770 --> 00:05:28.180 align:middle line:84%
the path of coming to oneness,
dissolving a separateness

00:05:28.180 --> 00:05:29.620 align:middle line:90%
through love.

00:05:29.620 --> 00:05:33.940 align:middle line:84%
It's a yoga, because it's a
part of a system that leads one

00:05:33.940 --> 00:05:37.630 align:middle line:84%
to experiencing reality, the
truth of the way things are

00:05:37.630 --> 00:05:40.590 align:middle line:84%
and who we really are
underneath who we think we are.

00:05:40.590 --> 00:05:43.040 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING CHANT]

00:05:43.040 --> 00:05:50.880 align:middle line:90%


00:05:50.880 --> 00:05:54.600 align:middle line:84%
>> The purpose of life to the
Bhakti yogi is about God--

00:05:54.600 --> 00:05:59.170 align:middle line:84%
every word, thought, and deed,
an offering to the Divine.

00:05:59.170 --> 00:06:04.000 align:middle line:84%
>> Bhakti is just
surrendering your own self--

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:06.890 align:middle line:90%
the I ego, the I concept--

00:06:06.890 --> 00:06:11.620 align:middle line:84%
to the lotus feet of God so
that you are emptying yourself.

00:06:11.620 --> 00:06:14.200 align:middle line:84%
>> It's to get ourself into
that state of receptivity,

00:06:14.200 --> 00:06:16.140 align:middle line:90%
of humility, of learning.

00:06:16.140 --> 00:06:19.750 align:middle line:84%
Then, we are receptive
to higher teachings,

00:06:19.750 --> 00:06:24.800 align:middle line:84%
higher frequency of love,
higher frequency of wisdom.

00:06:24.800 --> 00:06:29.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Traditionally, Bhakti is not
the physical practice of asana.

00:06:29.660 --> 00:06:34.235 align:middle line:84%
It focuses on music, mantras,
or chants called kirtan.

00:06:34.235 --> 00:06:37.700 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING CHANTS]

00:06:37.700 --> 00:06:49.610 align:middle line:90%


00:06:49.610 --> 00:06:53.090 align:middle line:84%
>> Kirtan is this practice of
repetition of what they call

00:06:53.090 --> 00:06:55.680 align:middle line:84%
the names of God,
the divine names.

00:06:55.680 --> 00:06:59.090 align:middle line:84%
>> Kirtan, in this realm,
it's the chanting of a mantra

00:06:59.090 --> 00:07:00.710 align:middle line:90%
and it's call and response.

00:07:00.710 --> 00:07:04.580 align:middle line:84%
So someone is leading it, and
then the group sings it back.

00:07:04.580 --> 00:07:06.020 align:middle line:90%
So it's a shared experience.

00:07:06.020 --> 00:07:08.750 align:middle line:84%
There's singing, and
there's also listening.

00:07:08.750 --> 00:07:10.700 align:middle line:90%
Both are equally important.

00:07:10.700 --> 00:07:12.140 align:middle line:90%
And that's part of the practice.

00:07:12.140 --> 00:07:15.116 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING CHANTS]

00:07:15.116 --> 00:07:28.020 align:middle line:90%


00:07:28.020 --> 00:07:30.155 align:middle line:84%
There's a power in the
mantras, in the names

00:07:30.155 --> 00:07:32.090 align:middle line:90%
that we're singing.

00:07:32.090 --> 00:07:34.040 align:middle line:84%
If you're doing Naam
Sankirtan, which

00:07:34.040 --> 00:07:38.160 align:middle line:84%
is the singing of the names
in a group, those names--

00:07:38.160 --> 00:07:43.820 align:middle line:84%
Ram, Shiva, Krishna,
Durga, Kali, Saraswati--

00:07:43.820 --> 00:07:46.310 align:middle line:84%
these are what they
call divine names that

00:07:46.310 --> 00:07:50.820 align:middle line:84%
have been transmitted to us
over the ages through the seers

00:07:50.820 --> 00:07:53.540 align:middle line:90%
and the rishis who receive them.

00:07:53.540 --> 00:07:56.820 align:middle line:84%
And when we hear them,
they resonate with us

00:07:56.820 --> 00:07:57.620 align:middle line:90%
in a certain way.

00:07:57.620 --> 00:08:00.980 align:middle line:84%
So no one has to tell you
that they mean anything.

00:08:00.980 --> 00:08:04.820 align:middle line:84%
You already know, because
they say that they are

00:08:04.820 --> 00:08:07.270 align:middle line:90%
the names of our own selves.

00:08:07.270 --> 00:08:10.700 align:middle line:84%
And we just have to
be reminded of them.

00:08:10.700 --> 00:08:12.320 align:middle line:84%
And so how do we
remind ourselves?

00:08:12.320 --> 00:08:13.940 align:middle line:90%
We just keep calling.

00:08:13.940 --> 00:08:16.070 align:middle line:84%
We keep calling,
just in the same way

00:08:16.070 --> 00:08:19.160 align:middle line:84%
you do an asana practice and
you do repetition of certain

00:08:19.160 --> 00:08:22.787 align:middle line:84%
poses so that you can feel
all the parts of your body.

00:08:22.787 --> 00:08:23.870 align:middle line:90%
How is your blood flowing?

00:08:23.870 --> 00:08:26.720 align:middle line:90%
Where is the prana flowing?

00:08:26.720 --> 00:08:29.510 align:middle line:84%
>> The chanting is like
cleansing the mirror

00:08:29.510 --> 00:08:30.550 align:middle line:90%
of the mind.

00:08:30.550 --> 00:08:33.890 align:middle line:84%
"Man" means mind, and
"tra" means to deliver.

00:08:33.890 --> 00:08:38.390 align:middle line:84%
A mantra is a way of cleaning
the mirror of the mind

00:08:38.390 --> 00:08:41.000 align:middle line:84%
so that we can actually
see our true self.

00:08:41.000 --> 00:08:43.780 align:middle line:90%


00:08:43.780 --> 00:08:47.860 align:middle line:84%
>> With chanting, you're
actually using your breath

00:08:47.860 --> 00:08:49.340 align:middle line:90%
and your voice.

00:08:49.340 --> 00:08:51.460 align:middle line:84%
And your body's
moving sometimes.

00:08:51.460 --> 00:08:53.800 align:middle line:84%
And there's also people around
you doing the same thing

00:08:53.800 --> 00:08:56.260 align:middle line:90%
that you're hearing.

00:08:56.260 --> 00:08:59.150 align:middle line:84%
And then of course,
your mind is there too.

00:08:59.150 --> 00:09:02.290 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to hold onto it
intellectually or emotionally.

00:09:02.290 --> 00:09:03.550 align:middle line:90%
That will pass.

00:09:03.550 --> 00:09:09.460 align:middle line:84%
Every repetition of one of these
names is a seed that's planted.

00:09:09.460 --> 00:09:12.580 align:middle line:84%
And that seed will grow
according to the conditions

00:09:12.580 --> 00:09:15.050 align:middle line:90%
and causes that arise.

00:09:15.050 --> 00:09:17.002 align:middle line:90%
So we're planting those seeds.

00:09:17.002 --> 00:09:19.210 align:middle line:84%
And then you go out and live
your life and be stupid.

00:09:19.210 --> 00:09:19.690 align:middle line:90%
It's OK.

00:09:19.690 --> 00:09:21.090 align:middle line:90%
But you're planting the seeds.

00:09:21.090 --> 00:09:23.640 align:middle line:84%
A farmer plants his seeds
and goes home and watches TV.

00:09:23.640 --> 00:09:26.240 align:middle line:84%
He doesn't sit there
and look at them.

00:09:26.240 --> 00:09:27.040 align:middle line:90%
It's two minutes.

00:09:27.040 --> 00:09:28.660 align:middle line:90%
They haven't grown.

00:09:28.660 --> 00:09:31.340 align:middle line:84%
You do your practices, and
then you live your life.

00:09:31.340 --> 00:09:37.710 align:middle line:90%


00:09:37.710 --> 00:09:41.140 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:09:41.140 --> 00:09:43.600 align:middle line:90%


00:09:43.600 --> 00:09:46.720 align:middle line:84%
>> Mystical Bhakti, the
tradition of the Bauls,

00:09:46.720 --> 00:09:50.680 align:middle line:84%
has its philosophical roots in
Bhakti yet draws on traditions

00:09:50.680 --> 00:09:52.645 align:middle line:84%
of erotic poetry
applied to music.

00:09:52.645 --> 00:09:56.676 align:middle line:90%


00:09:56.676 --> 00:09:59.520 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:09:59.520 --> 00:10:04.220 align:middle line:84%
>> What Sufis are to
Islam, Bauls are to Hindus.

00:10:04.220 --> 00:10:05.020 align:middle line:90%
Yes?

00:10:05.020 --> 00:10:06.580 align:middle line:84%
They have a
transcendental quality

00:10:06.580 --> 00:10:09.460 align:middle line:90%
to them, a little bit madness.

00:10:09.460 --> 00:10:13.000 align:middle line:84%
They don't fit into the social
realm, social structure.

00:10:13.000 --> 00:10:15.580 align:middle line:84%
A Baul is not a
puritanical being.

00:10:15.580 --> 00:10:20.330 align:middle line:84%
He is willing to be intoxicated
by love, intoxicated by life.

00:10:20.330 --> 00:10:27.320 align:middle line:10%
>> Baul is just a way to attain
nirvana, or moksha, or God,

00:10:27.320 --> 00:10:31.900 align:middle line:10%
whatever you want to attain
through the practice of love.

00:10:31.900 --> 00:10:35.740 align:middle line:84%
You are thinking your
partner to be not

00:10:35.740 --> 00:10:38.170 align:middle line:90%
a person but an instrument--

00:10:38.170 --> 00:10:43.430 align:middle line:84%
an instrument to elevate
yourself, your mind.

00:10:43.430 --> 00:10:45.820 align:middle line:84%
So you are actually
making love to your mind

00:10:45.820 --> 00:10:48.370 align:middle line:90%
through another body.

00:10:48.370 --> 00:10:51.170 align:middle line:84%
Primary practice
is to erase the--

00:10:51.170 --> 00:10:53.170 align:middle line:90%
>> Physical desire, the lust.

00:10:53.170 --> 00:10:55.345 align:middle line:84%
>> Everything happening
is spiritually happening.

00:10:55.345 --> 00:10:56.220 align:middle line:90%
There is no religion.

00:10:56.220 --> 00:10:57.790 align:middle line:90%
There is no ritual.

00:10:57.790 --> 00:11:02.140 align:middle line:84%
>> The devotional aspect of it
is so magnificent, the songs,

00:11:02.140 --> 00:11:05.542 align:middle line:90%
they take you out of body.

00:11:05.542 --> 00:11:08.494 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:11:08.494 --> 00:11:13.920 align:middle line:90%


00:11:13.920 --> 00:11:15.660 align:middle line:90%
>> It's all heart.

00:11:15.660 --> 00:11:18.120 align:middle line:84%
Most of their
songs are longing--

00:11:18.120 --> 00:11:19.800 align:middle line:90%
longing or celebration.

00:11:19.800 --> 00:11:23.460 align:middle line:84%
And even if the man is singing,
he or she will sing as a woman.

00:11:23.460 --> 00:11:27.150 align:middle line:84%
>> In Baul philosophy, I believe
myself, when I make love,

00:11:27.150 --> 00:11:28.210 align:middle line:90%
I'm a woman.

00:11:28.210 --> 00:11:32.430 align:middle line:84%
Krishna is the one and
only man in this universe.

00:11:32.430 --> 00:11:34.180 align:middle line:90%
And we all are women.

00:11:34.180 --> 00:11:36.720 align:middle line:84%
And we are making
love to Krishna.

00:11:36.720 --> 00:11:39.990 align:middle line:84%
>> This is about the feminine
aspect of consciousness.

00:11:39.990 --> 00:11:41.585 align:middle line:84%
Shiva, for example,
is very masculine

00:11:41.585 --> 00:11:42.960 align:middle line:90%
if you look at his body.

00:11:42.960 --> 00:11:44.406 align:middle line:90%
But look at his face--

00:11:44.406 --> 00:11:45.780 align:middle line:84%
if you look at
the face of Shiva,

00:11:45.780 --> 00:11:47.345 align:middle line:90%
it will be very, very feminine.

00:11:47.345 --> 00:11:49.230 align:middle line:84%
There will be a
gentleness on the face--

00:11:49.230 --> 00:11:50.980 align:middle line:90%
no aggression on the face.

00:11:50.980 --> 00:11:53.490 align:middle line:84%
So ultimately, for
the being to be awake,

00:11:53.490 --> 00:11:56.880 align:middle line:84%
he or she has to get in touch
with the feminine aspect

00:11:56.880 --> 00:11:59.020 align:middle line:90%
of consciousness.

00:11:59.020 --> 00:12:03.540 align:middle line:10%
>> We believe in love, and Baul
