00:23:48.850 --> 00:23:50.530 align:middle line:90%
together or going out to eat.

00:23:50.530 --> 00:23:54.490 align:middle line:84%
It's to gather together to
go deeper into the truth

00:23:54.490 --> 00:23:58.140 align:middle line:84%
and to help each
other find the truth.

00:23:58.140 --> 00:24:03.160 align:middle line:84%
>> In typical satsang, where
if it's led by a teacher,

00:24:03.160 --> 00:24:05.920 align:middle line:84%
you would have the teacher
giving a discourse potentially

00:24:05.920 --> 00:24:09.370 align:middle line:84%
on the teachings of the guru
in that particular lineage

00:24:09.370 --> 00:24:10.930 align:middle line:90%
or readings.

00:24:10.930 --> 00:24:12.850 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, it's even
a Q&A where you're

00:24:12.850 --> 00:24:16.450 align:middle line:84%
discussing matters of the
heart, matters of life,

00:24:16.450 --> 00:24:19.050 align:middle line:84%
but then also doing
practice together.

00:24:19.050 --> 00:24:22.270 align:middle line:84%
>> There's more power in
the energy of the group than

00:24:22.270 --> 00:24:25.020 align:middle line:90%
on individual practice.

00:24:25.020 --> 00:24:27.220 align:middle line:84%
And this is quite
obvious if you come

00:24:27.220 --> 00:24:31.630 align:middle line:84%
to an ashram like this, what
