00:25:10.000 --> 00:25:13.240 align:middle line:84%
you're going to hang out
with is your previous karmas

00:25:13.240 --> 00:25:15.430 align:middle line:90%
manifesting themselves.

00:25:15.430 --> 00:25:18.610 align:middle line:84%
So you begin to see that
you surround yourself

00:25:18.610 --> 00:25:21.270 align:middle line:84%
with things that will help
you satisfy your desires,

00:25:21.270 --> 00:25:22.070 align:middle line:90%
what you want.

00:25:22.070 --> 00:25:24.910 align:middle line:90%


00:25:24.910 --> 00:25:28.590 align:middle line:84%
>> Another powerful technique
often used in the three margas

00:25:28.590 --> 00:25:29.830 align:middle line:90%
is japa.

00:25:29.830 --> 00:25:32.680 align:middle line:84%
Unlike kirtan that
have no fixed form,

00:25:32.680 --> 00:25:35.560 align:middle line:84%
japa uses very
specific repetitions

00:25:35.560 --> 00:25:38.410 align:middle line:84%
that focus the mind and
harness subtle energies

00:25:38.410 --> 00:25:42.890 align:middle line:84%
meant to achieve an inner
evolution of consciousness.

00:25:42.890 --> 00:25:48.260 align:middle line:10%
>> Japa practice is the
repetition of a special name

00:25:48.260 --> 00:25:51.590 align:middle line:10%
or a word or a syllable that's
been given as a particular

00:25:51.590 --> 00:25:52.400 align:middle line:10%
practice.

00:25:52.400 --> 00:25:56.960 align:middle line:84%
In many traditions in India,
your teacher, or your lineage,

00:25:56.960 --> 00:26:00.290 align:middle line:84%
